psShapingStatusOper.name: psShapingStatusOper
psShapingStatusOper.description: This object reflects the current operational traffic shaping status of the PacketShaper. The value of this object reflects the status of the front panel status LED. If all of the following conditions are true, then the object is set to 1, otherwise it is 2: links are up, shaping is on, and the siterouter is usable (if configured).

psAlarmMeasurementEngineCount.description: The number of psAlarmMeasurementEngine traps sent by the agent since the last reset.

psAlarmMeasurementEngineStatus.name: psAlarmMeasurementEngineStatus
psAlarmMeasurementEngineStatus.description: The current status of the Measurement Engine. The values enumerated above correspond to those shown in the command line 'me show' command. (1) initially starting (2) starting (3) running (4) error on volume (5) disabled (6) wait to start (7) suspended (8) backing up data (9) restoring data

psAlarmMeasurementEngine.name: psAlarmMeasurementEngine
psAlarmMeasurementEngine.description: A psAlarmMeasurementEngine trap signifies that the Measurement Engine has changed to a state of less readiness, or failed on startup.

psAlarmStandbyCount.name: psAlarmStandbyCount
psAlarmStandbyCount.description: The number of psAlarmStandby traps sent by the agent since the last reset.

psAlarmStandbyStatus.name: psAlarmStandbyStatus
psAlarmStandbyStatus.description: Status of the standby feature. A status of not-configured(1) means that standby is not configured for this PacketShaper. active(2) means hot standby is processing traffic according to its shaping mode. passive(3) means hot standby is not processing traffic but is monitoring the active partner of the paired PacketShapers. down(4) means hot standby has declared itself ineligible for active mode due to a self-detected fault. direct(5) means standby direct is processing and copying traffic to its partner. disconnected(6) means standby direct is non-functional since it cannot reach its partner. leak(7) means the Packetshaper has detected a loop in the network and so has disabled the stanby direct functionality and is only processing traffic flowing through it. disable(8) means that the standby direct feature has been disabled and is non-functional.

psAlarmStandby.name: psAlarmStandby
psAlarmStandby.description: A psAlarmStandby trap signifies that the standby status of the device has changed to a state of less readiness. The psAlarmStandbyStatus variable included with this trap provides more information.

psAlarmFanThree.name: psAlarmFanThree
psAlarmFanThree.description: A psAlarmFanThree trap signifies that 3rd fan of the device has failed.

psAlarmFanThreeCount.name: psAlarmFanThreeCount
psAlarmFanThreeCount.description: The number of psAlarmFanThree traps sent by the agent since the last reset.

psAlarmFanThreeStatus.name: psAlarmFanThreeStatus
psAlarmFanThreeStatus.description: The operational status of the 3rd fan of the device. (0) Not existant (1) UP (2) DOWN

psAlarmFanFour.name: psAlarmFanFour
psAlarmFanFour.description: A psAlarmFanFour trap signifies that 4th fan of the device has failed.

psAlarmFanFourCount.name: psAlarmFanFourCount
psAlarmFanFourCount.description: The number of psAlarmFanFour traps sent by the agent since the last reset.

psAlarmFanFourStatus.name: psAlarmFanFourStatus
psAlarmFanFourStatus.description: The operational status of the 4th fan of the device. (0) Not existant (1) UP (2) DOWN

trapDestTable.name: trapDestTable
trapDestTable.description: A list of destinations for traps emitted from this PacketShaper

trapDestEntry.name: trapDestEntry
trapDestEntry.description: A trap destination entry containing the IP address (and possibly other information in the future)

trapDestIpAddr.name: trapDestIpAddr
trapDestIpAddr.description: An address to which traps are sent

trapDestStatus.name: trapDestStatus
trapDestStatus.description: Status of this trap destination. Setting to invalid(2) is equivalent to removing the address from the table. See also trapDestRemove for a shortcut for removal.

trapDestAdd.name: trapDestAdd
trapDestAdd.description: A shortcut for adding a host to trapDestTable. If the name is not in n.n.n.n IP address form, then the agent attempts to look it up via DNS. If the operation fails with BADVALUE, try again with an IP address. The associated IP address is added to the trapDestTable if the operation succeeded. The table should be queried afterward to insure that the action took place.

trapDestRemove.name: trapDestRemove
trapDestRemove.description: A shortcut for removing an IP address from trapDestTable. If the name is not in n.n.n.n IP address form, then the agent attempts to look it up via DNS. If the operation fails with BADVALUE, try again with an IP address. The table should be queried afterward to insure that the action took place.

psShapingStatusAdmin.name: psShapingStatusAdmin
psShapingStatusAdmin.description: This object reflects the current configured traffic shaping status of the PacketShaper. The value of other(4) may occur in certain cases which can only be caused through the PacketShaper's user interface, and cannot be set through this variable

userEventTrapName.name: userEventTrapName
userEventTrapName.description: The name of the user event which has occurred.

userEventTrapExpression.name: userEventTrapExpression
userEventTrapExpression.description: The expression defining this user event.

userEventTrapVariable.name: userEventTrapVariable
userEventTrapVariable.description: The name of the Measurement Engine variable which is tested in this user event.

userEventTrapElementType.name: userEventTrapElementType
userEventTrapElementType.description: The type of element which is tested in this user event.

userEventTrapRegid.name: userEventTrapRegid
userEventTrapRegid.description: The registration of this user event.

userEventTrapValue.name: userEventTrapValue
userEventTrapValue.description: The value of userEventTrapVariable which triggered the event.

userEventTrapTarget.name: userEventTrapTarget
userEventTrapTarget.description: The name of the link, class, or partition, as given in userEventTrapElementType, which is the target of this event regiatration.

userEventTrapThreshold.name: userEventTrapThreshold
userEventTrapThreshold.description: The threshold value which triggers this event. See the value of userEventTrapExpression for the signedness with respect to the threshold (<, >, etc.)

userEventTrapRearm.name: userEventTrapRearm
userEventTrapRearm.description: The rearm value which must be hit after an occurrence of this event in order to rearm it. See the value of userEventTrapExpression for the signedness with respect to the threshold (<, >, etc.)

userEventTrapDayCount.name: userEventTrapDayCount
userEventTrapDayCount.description: The number of times this event has occurred on this day (as counted from midnight to midnight, local time). If this value is greater than or equal to userEventTrapDayLimit, and that value is non-zero, then no more instances of this event will be reported until the next day.

userEventTrapDayLimit.name: userEventTrapDayLimit
userEventTrapDayLimit.description: The maximum number of times this event is allowed to occur per day (as counted from midnight to midnight, local time), as configured by the user. A value of zero denotes no limit.

psAlarmUserEvent.name: psAlarmUserEvent
psAlarmUserEvent.description: A psAlarmUserEvent trap signifies that a user event, which has been registered by the user, has occurred. The associated variables give more information on the event.

agentEventTrapName.name: agentEventTrapName
agentEventTrapName.description: The name of the agent instance which has fired the event.

agentEventTrapType.name: agentEventTrapType
agentEventTrapType.description: The type of event that occurred, 0 = GREEN, 1 = RED, 2 = YELLOW, 3 = BLUE.

agentEventTrapDescription.name: agentEventTrapDescription
agentEventTrapDescription.description: A description of the event that has occurred.

psAlarmAgentEvent.name: psAlarmAgentEvent
psAlarmAgentEvent.description: A psAlarmAgentEvent trap signifies that an agent event, which has been triggered by the user, has occurred. The associated variables give more information on the event.

psFeatureHighAvDeviceDown.name: psFeatureHighAvDeviceDown
psFeatureHighAvDeviceDown.description: A psFeatureHighAvDeviceFailed trap signifies that an interface or router we are tracking has gone down. If it is an interface that went down, the bindings will show the corresponding router and the name of the interface which went down. The name will be specified as 'unknown' if we could not resolve the interface name. But if it is the router that went down, the interface name will not be specified.

psFeatureHighAvDeviceDownCount.name: psFeatureHighAvDeviceDownCount
psFeatureHighAvDeviceDownCount.description: The number of psFeatureHighAvDevice traps sent by the agent since the last reset.

psFeatureHighAvDeviceDownStatus.name: psFeatureHighAvDeviceDownStatus
psFeatureHighAvDeviceDownStatus.description: The operational status of the interface of the router we are polling. (1) UP (2) DOWN.

psFeatureHighAvDeviceDownRouter.name: psFeatureHighAvDeviceDownRouter
psFeatureHighAvDeviceDownRouter.description: The name of a router that has gone down or the name of the router whose one of the interfaces has gone down.

psFeatureHighAvDeviceDownInterface.name: psFeatureHighAvDeviceDownInterface
psFeatureHighAvDeviceDownInterface.description: The name of the interface that has gone down. The name will be specified as 'unknown' in the cases where we could not resolve the interface name. The interface name will have a value of NULL or zero-length value if the router goes down.
